Industries


Investment Services & Portfolio Management




Company Description


Baldwin Investment Management invests in US and foreign based companies with market-caps greater than $2.5 billion. They look for industry leaders with proven management teams, who provide innovative products and research and whose earnings growth is in excess of their industry peers. The firm employs fundamental, quantitative and technical analysis in the selection process. They also offer alternative investments in venture capital, real estate development and through various insurance products.Baldwin's proprietary quantitative stock selection model identifies global companies that exhibit superior price and earnings growth patterns, with a lesser but significant focus on price- earnings and price-to-sales attributes. They begin with a universe of over 800 stocks, applying their formula to each in order to assign decile rankings. From the stock universe, they select and maintain a working list of about 150 stocks. Baldwin looks for stocks with consistently high rankings and appropriate sector representation.  Portfolio managers meet frequently to discuss the relative growth potential of each stock sector. Larger stock positions or a greater number of stocks are purchased within sectors with strong growth prospects, while smaller positions or fewer stocks are chosen within less favored sectors.Baldwin also maintains a comprehensive stock research database. Each portfolio manager focuses on one or more equity sectors. Their qualitative opinions, culled from a wide diversity of Wall Street and independent sources, are regularly added to the stock research database.The firm's technical approach consists of reviewing a variety of technical price charts for companies within their stock universe. These charts may serve as early warning indicators for companies poised to out- or under- perform the market. They use this information to assist in their timing of stock purchases and sales and to further enhance investment performance.




